doc.after: As of 2015, Vanderbilt had an enrollment of 6,851 undergraduate and 5,874 graduate and professional students, for a total of 12,725 students.[42] Students from all 50 states and more than 90 countries attend Vanderbilt, with 59% of the total student body coming from outside the Southeast; 9.5% of students are from outside the United States.[7][42][43] Moreover, 24% of the undergraduate class of 2010 was non-Caucasian, while roughly half were women.[44] As of 2014, the incoming class was 50% male and 50% female.[3]
